        "subject": "LU-6142 utils: Fix compile warning in lfs_project",
        "message": "LU-6142 utils: Fix compile warning in lfs_project\n\nIn strncpy(), providing size less than destination\nwill leave last byte untouch. This is what the\ncompiler is complaining about. Since, strncpy()\ngurantees NUL termination for anyting after length\nof source. The correct usage is to provide the\nfull length of destination.\n\n$ uname -r\n6.12.0-124.20.1.el10_1.x86_64\n\n$ gcc --version\ngcc (GCC) 14.3.1 20250617\n\nlfs_project.c: In function ‘project_clear_one’:\nlfs_project.c:258:17: error: ‘strncpy’ output may be truncated copying 255 bytes from a string of length 255 [-Werror=stringop-truncation]\n  258 |                 strncpy(lp.project_name, bname, NAME_MAX);\n      |                 ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\nlfs_project.c: In function ‘project_set_one’:\nlfs_project.c:219:17: error: ‘strncpy’ output may be truncated copying 255 bytes from a string of length 255 [-Werror=stringop-truncation]\n  219 |                 strncpy(lp.project_name, bname, NAME_MAX);\n      |                 ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nChange-Id: Ic09e5a70e9651ea6855d297c83932755a44e848e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
